def: Possessing the same number of factors of a given kind; as, ahomogeneous polynomial.
A weapon resembling a hammer, often having one side of the headpointed; -- used by horsemen in the Middle Ages to break armor.Fairholt.
Producing fumes; fumous. "Drowned in fumy wine." H. Brooke.
Any affection of the muscles or muscular system.
Of or pertaining to the region of the eye and the nose; as, theoculonasal, or nasal, nerve, one of the branches of the ophthalmic.

One of the stages in the life history of certain rusts(Uredinales), regarded at one time as a distinct genus. It is asummer stage preceding the teleutospore, or winter stage. SeeUredinales, in the Supplement.
A form of machine for dressing the surface of wood, metal,stone, etc.
One skilled in coat armor or heraldry. Cussans.
To reduce to a code, as laws.
One who, or that which, proves.
